WHO   — THE INTERFACE — a metaxy sphere — the between
WHAT  — Everything that exchanges with the world does it through a surface: the cell through its membrane, the body through its skin, the program through its interface, two people through the words between them. The interface is the thinnest part of any system and the most important — where inside meets outside, where two worlds touch without becoming one. To control the interface is to control the exchange.
WHERE — the between — the domain that belongs to neither side  Framework inputs: the threshold; the boundary; the two worlds it joins  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Everything that exchanges with the world does it through a surface: the cell through its membrane, the body through its skin, the program through its interface, two people through the words between them. The interface is the thinnest part of any system and the most important — where inside meets outside, where two worlds touch without becoming one. To control the interface is to control the exchange.
HOW   — Crystallized from the public record.

